      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BORROLOOLA BOY (6) ran a good time (16.69) winning a Restricted WIN two back at Healesville but missed the frame latest finishing sixth at Healesville. Has the ability and expected to bounce back. FIRE UP MARK (4) is in top form notching back to back wins, the latest over 390m in (22.45) at Warrnambool. Has never missed the frame from three starts from this draw, including a win. Hard to fault his form and he makes plenty of appeal. UNIVERSE (2) turned in a moderate run last time when sixth at Shepparton over 450m behind Zipping Koster (25.98) in a Rank Limit - Grade 5. Can do much better this time. HEATHCOTE RUPEE (7) is a last-start placegetter at this track and distance - should be thereabouts.",
